SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS ORGANIZED AS A MINNESOTA NONPROFIT CORPORATION AND HAS BEEN RECOGNIZED BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS) AS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC) SECTION 501(A) AS ORGANIZATIONS DESCRIBED IN IRC SECTION 501(C)(3), QUALIFY FOR THE CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTION DEDUCTION UNDER IRC SECTIONS 170(B)(1)(A), AND HAS BEEN DETERMINED NOT TO BE A PRIVATE FOUNDATION UNDER IRC SECTIONS 509(A)(2). THE ORGANIZATION IS ANNUALLY REQUIRED TO FILE A RETURN OF ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAX (FORM 990) WITH THE IRS. IN ADDITION, THE ORGANIZATION IS SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX ON NET INCOME THAT IS DERIVED FROM BUSINESS ACTIVITIES THAT ARE UNRELATED TO ITS EXEMPT PURPOSE. THE ORGANIZATION HAS DETERMINED THAT IT IS NOT SUBJECT TO UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME TAX AND HAS NOT FILED AN EXEMPT ORGANIZATION BUSINESS INCOME TAX RETURN (FORM 990-T) WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT HAVE ANY COMMITTEES THAT HAVE AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY THE EXTERNAL AUDITOR. FORM 990 IS SENT TO THE FISCAL DIRECTOR FOR REVIEW, THEN REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE MANAGEMENT COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS NEGOTIATES AND APPROVES COMPENSATION FOR ALL STAFF, TOP OFFICIALS AND OFFICERS. SALARIES AND BENEFITS ARE COMPARED TO SALARY AND COMPENSATION DATA FROM THE MINNESOTA COUNCIL OF NON-PROFITS AND OTHER SALARY SURVEYS AS AVAILABLE. THIS COMPARISON IS CONDUCTED BIANNUALLY. THE ENTIRE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RATIFIES THE DECISION ON COMPENSATION AND DOCUMENTS THE DECISION IN THE BOARD MINUTES. THE LAST REVIEW AND APPROVAL WAS CONDUCTED FOR ALL POSITIONS IN JUNE 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPEACTION UPON WRITTEN REQUEST TO WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT, INC.
THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ASSUMES RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT.
